Tropical Fern Functional Traits

Leaf Traits Figures

This document contains summary statistics for the 2017 La Selva field work. Below are visualizations for many of the leaf functional traits we measured including SLA, stomatal density, cholorophyll content, lamina length and lamina area.

Hydrauliic Traits Figures

This document contains summary statistics for the 2017 La Selva field work. Below are visualizations for many of the hyrdaulic traits we derived from pressure volume curves. These traits are calculated from Sackss excel macro. I have deleted the climber catergory for ease of viewing.

Frond tissue isotopes

iso <- read.csv("raw_data/fern_isotopes.csv")
iso <- merge(iso, niche, by="species")

par(mgp=c(2.5,1,0), mar=c(4,4,1,1), cex.lab=1.1)
boxplot(d13C ~ niche, data = iso, xaxt='n',outline=FALSE,
        ylab=expression(Frond~{delta}^13*C~~('\211')))
axis(1, niche_lab, at=1:4, cex=1.1)

boxplot(d15N ~ niche, data = iso, xaxt='n',outline=FALSE,
        ylab=expression(Frond~{delta}^15*N~~('\211')))
axis(1, niche_lab, at=1:4, cex=1.1)
